No Preview

Sorry, but you either have no stories or none are selected somehow.

  • Please check the Storybook config.
  • Try reloading the page.

If the problem persists, check the browser console, or the terminal you've run Storybook from.

The component failed to render properly, likely due to a configuration issue in Storybook. Here are some common causes and how you can address them:

  1. Missing Context/Providers: You can use decorators to supply specific contexts or providers, which are sometimes necessary for components to render correctly. For detailed instructions on using decorators, please visit the Decorators documentation.
  2. Misconfigured Webpack or Vite: Verify that Storybook picks up all necessary settings for loaders, plugins, and other relevant parameters. You can find step-by-step guides for configuring Webpack or Vite with Storybook.
  3. Missing Environment Variables: Your Storybook may require specific environment variables to function as intended. You can set up custom environment variables as outlined in the Environment Variables documentation.

Map

The map presents data that has a location component.

Usage

Use a map when it's beneficial to users to show the information in the geographical context. The map can also calculate the distance from the user's location to the destination.

Locations props

The following props are provided by Card Location:

LinkObject = {
  href: "link-href",
  target: "link-target",
};

MediaObject = {
  src: "img-src",
  alt: "img-alt",
};

locations: [
  {
    name: "Title",
    type: "Type",
    address: "Address",
    phone: "518-555-0163",
    directions_link: {
      link: LinkObject,
    },
    coordinates: { lng: -73.90731352349589, lat: 40.709278509963205 },
    open_hours: "Day - Day: 0:00AM - 0:00PM",
    services: ["Service Type 1", "Service Type 2", "Service Type 3", "Service Type 4", "Service Type 5"],
    image: MediaObject,
    icon: "defaultMarker", // or "campusMarker", "hospitalMarker", "apccMarker", "specialtyCareMarker", "nutritionMarker", "dentalMarker", "bhsadMarker", "schoolHealthMarker", "clinicalAffilitationsMarker"
  },
  // (...)
];

Highlights props

The following props are available:

MediaObject = {
  src: "img-src",
  alt: "img-alt",
};

highlights: [
  {
    name: "Title",
    description: "Description",
    coordinates: { lng: -74.1, lat: 40.716071217271164 },
    cover: MediaObject,
    icon: MediaObject,
  },
  // (...)
];

Legend props

The following props are available:

legend: [
  {
    icon: "defaultMarker", // or "campusMarker", "hospitalMarker", "apccMarker", "specialtyCareMarker", "nutritionMarker", "dentalMarker", "bhsadMarker", "schoolHealthMarker", "clinicalAffilitationsMarker"
    name: "Location",
  },
  // (...)
];
